307
00:22:50,520 --> 00:22:52,200
These men are right on the edge

308
00:22:52,280 --> 00:22:53,560
and he wants to rile
them up more

309
00:22:53,600 --> 00:22:55,640
by talking about a lying,
thieving captain,

310
00:22:55,680 --> 00:22:58,680
then stand on a deserted beach
and talk about an election.

311
00:22:58,760 --> 00:23:01,720
Before you know it, half a dozen men
will have laid claim to the captaincy.

312
00:23:01,760 --> 00:23:03,400
Camps will divide.

313
00:23:03,480 --> 00:23:05,640
It won't be dark yet
before the fighting starts.

314
00:23:07,840 --> 00:23:10,160
We're gonna see Flint
pay for his crimes.

315
00:23:10,200 --> 00:23:12,600
But we'll do it at home

316
00:23:12,680 --> 00:23:15,320
and we'll do it
like civilized men.

317
00:23:15,400 --> 00:23:17,960
That's how we avoid the abyss.

318
00:23:19,600 --> 00:23:22,040
We knew you spent the night
drinking together.

319
00:23:22,120 --> 00:23:24,440
How can we take you
at your word?

320
00:23:27,680 --> 00:23:29,680
You don't have to take my word.

321
00:23:36,040 --> 00:23:37,720
