00:28:33,240 --> 00:28:35,400
I'm sorry.

422
00:28:42,240 --> 00:28:43,880
I came to lend
credence to your case

423
00:28:43,960 --> 00:28:46,040
that the Urca
is still to be won.

424
00:28:57,400 --> 00:28:59,480
What the fuck
are you doing to him?

425
00:28:59,520 --> 00:29:01,880
- Making sure there's nothing
incriminating... - Stop. Stop.

426
00:29:03,680 --> 00:29:05,560
There's no way out of this.

427
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:09,240
Take it from me,

428
00:29:09,280 --> 00:29:11,520
there's always a way.

429
00:29:20,280 --> 00:29:22,080
Sir.

430
00:29:27,800 --> 00:29:30,280
- What is it? - A small band of men were
seen approaching the fort

431
00:29:30,320 --> 00:29:33,560
from the west this morning.
No one's been able to identify them.

432
00:29:33,640 --> 00:29:35,040
Are all the home crews
accounted for?

433
00:29:35,040 --> 00:29:36,880
Aye. Every one.
They had nothing to do with this.

434
00:29:36,920 --> 00:29:39,200
<i>Could this be a first move by England</i>
<i>to reclaim the island?</i>

435
00:29:39,240 --> 00:29:40,640
<i>Without a single ship involved?</i>

436
00:29:40,720 --> 00:29:43,480
This does not have the air of
a state move. This is something else.

