can I do?"

463
00:31:39,200 --> 00:31:41,000
<i>You can call this murder.</i>

464
00:31:41,080 --> 00:31:42,560
<i>A number of the men</i>
<i>might even believe you,</i>

465
00:31:42,640 --> 00:31:45,480
but will that be enough

466
00:31:45,560 --> 00:31:47,600
to stop this fight
that is about to happen?

467
00:31:49,000 --> 00:31:51,640
<i>Because if it's not,</i>
<i>a fight we might win</i>

468
00:31:51,680 --> 00:31:54,040
<i>becomes a battle</i>
<i>we are doomed to lose.</i>

469
00:31:54,080 --> 00:31:57,760
<i>Because the men went into it</i>
<i>infected with your suspicions,</i>

470
00:31:57,800 --> 00:32:00,760
<i>with your doubts.</i>

471
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:05,520
So, Mr. Quartermaster,

472
00:32:05,600 --> 00:32:08,640
is that truly what's
in their best interests?

473
00:32:29,320 --> 00:32:31,000
St. Augustine.

474
00:32:31,040 --> 00:32:32,320
Beg pardon?

475
00:32:32,400 --> 00:32:33,520
When the warship draws close,

476
00:32:33,600 --> 00:32:35,280
